subject: Re: [Read_Alphabet] Where's everyone gone?
msgSnippet: Tinyallen: I ve been using QS for years and don t plan on quitting as it is not a passing interest with me. I have been busy and have not checked the
messageBody:
Tinyallen:

I've been using QS for years and don't plan on quitting as it is not a "passing interest" with me.  I have been busy and have not checked the Ikonboard for awhile.  I also get tired of receiving the unending Shavian posts about how and when they should use "err" and "array."  I would like to see more activity on Read_Alphabet, but I must assume many people are busy with their summer vacations or other activities.
I can't look at Ikonboard now, but I'll try to check it out as soon as I can.

Paige Gabhart

tinyallen wrote:

    I've finally gotten to the point where I can not only read
QuickScript reliably (though slowly), but can write it almost useably
fast.
   Now the party's over and everyone's gone. The Ikonboard
(Shavian.org?) is almost as quiet. Is this just a bad season?

   I was hoping to get some feedback on my font's lettershapes so I
can start the hand-kerning process. Any comments, anyone?
   Anyone?
